cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DL

The paper discusses the challenges of retrieving relevant publications in the biomedical domain due to the variability and ambiguity of terms. This problem is closely related to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a platform that uses AI to label terms precisely, which falls under the scope of AI and machine learning (cs.AI), as well as deep learning (cs.LG) and deep neural networks (cs.DL).
